In a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, @veggie stock concentrate{1}, 3/4 cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4 servings), and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and cut @onion{1} into 1/2-inch-thick wedges; mince a few wedges until you have 2 TBSP (4 TBSP for 4). Halve, core, and thinly slice @green bell pepper{1} into strips. Trim stems from @portobello mushrooms{2}; thinly slice into strips. Zest and quarter @lime{1}. Dice @tomato{1} into 1/4-inch pieces.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{drizzle} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add onion wedges, bell pepper, and mushrooms. Season with @fajita spice blend{1%tablespoon}, a big pinch of @salt{pinch}, and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until veggies are browned and tender, ~{5-7%minutes}. (For 4 servings, work in batches.)

Turn off heat; stir in a squeeze of lime juice (big squeeze for 4).

== Pico de Gallo ==

While veggies cook, in a #small bowl{}, combine tomato, minced onion, juice from two lime wedges (four wedges for 4 servings), a pinch of salt, and pepper.

== Tortillas ==

When rice is almost done, wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp paper towels and microwave until warm and pliable, ~{30-60%seconds}.

== Queso ==

Place @queso blanco{3%ounce} in a separate #small microwave-safe bowl{}. Cover tightly with plastic wrap and microwave until warmed through, ~{1-2%minutes}. Carefully uncover (steam may release!) and stir.

> If you added any other items to your meal (apps, sides, and/or dessert), you can get started on them now!

== Assembly ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in 1 TBSP of @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) and as much lime zest as you like.

Transfer fajita veggies to a #serving platter{}. Serve family style with rice, tortillas, queso, pico de gallo, @sour cream{3%tablespoon}, and any remaining lime wedges so everyone can build their own fajitas.

> Don't forget to serve with any extra items you may have ordered to build out your meal!